        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 22. Distribution of Calophytus spp. collecting records throughout New Caledonia. Provinces are labelled and ecoregions delineated by colour." , "Figure 13. Calophytus matilei sp. nov. A adult male (MEI 135018), oblique view B same, lateral view C adult female (MEI 071892), oblique view D same, lateral view. Body length: male: 8.0 mm; female: 9.4 mm." , "Figure 7. Wings of Calophytus gen. nov. and Jeanchazeauia gen. nov. A C. chazeaui sp. nov. B C. schlingeri sp. nov. C C. grandiosus sp. nov. D C. matilei sp. nov. E C. webbi sp. nov. F C. monteithi sp. nov. G J. amoa sp. nov. H J. nubilosus sp. nov. (female) (figures not to scale)." , "Figure 6. Scutum and scutellum of Calophytus gen. nov. and Jeanchazeauia gen. nov. A C. schlingeri sp. nov. B C. grandiosus sp. nov. C C. matilei sp. nov. D C. webbi sp. nov. E J. nubilosus sp. nov. (figures not to scale) (drawings by J. Marie Metz)." , "Figure 14. Calophytus matilei sp. nov., cleared male genitalia A aedeagus, lateral view B gonocoxites, ventral view C epandrium. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." , "Figure 5. Lateral view of antennae of Calophytus gen. nov. A C. chazeaui sp. nov. B C. grandiosus sp. nov. C C. schlingeri sp. nov. D C. matilei sp. nov. E C. webbi sp. nov. (figures not to scale) (drawings by J. Marie Metz)." ;
